1. Cascade - Controls what happens to related entities when the parent changes.
  1.1 Persist Use: When you save parent -> child saves automatically
    @OneToMany(cascade = CascadeType.PERSIST)

  1.2 Merge Use: When you update parent -> child updates automatically
    @OneToMany(cascade = CascadeType.MERGE)

  1.3 Remove Use: When you delete parent -> child deleted automatically
    @OneToMany(cascade = CascadeType.REMOVE)

  1.4 Refresh Use: Refresh child when parent refreshed
    @OneToMany(cascade = CascadeType.REFRESH)

  1.5 Detach Use: Removes child from persistence context
    @OneToMany(cascade = CascadeType.DEACH)

  1.6 All Use: uses all cascade options
    @OneToMany(cascade = CascadeType.ALL)


2. Fetch - Controls loading timing.
  2.1 Eager Use: Load immediately
    @ManyToOne(fetch = FetchType.EAGER)

  2.2 Lazy Use: Load only when accessed
    @ManyToOne(fetch = FetchType.LAZY)


3. Optional - Controls whether a relationship is required
  3.1 True (default) Use: Relationship can be null
      @ManyToOne(optional = true)

  3.2 False Use: Relationship is absolutely required.
      @ManyToOne(optional = false)


4. OrphanRemoval - Controls if a child with no parents is removed
  4.1 True Use: if a parent is removed, so is its child
  4.2 False Use: if a parent is removed, the child isn't


5. TargetEntity - explicitly specifies the related class
    Use: When type cannot be inferred automatically.


6. @JoinColumn attributes -> control foreign key column. These define physical database column behavior.
  6.1 Name Use: Defines column name

  6.2 Nullable -> Controls NULL allowed
      nullable = false -> required
      nullable = true -> optional

  6.3 unique -> Ensures uniqueness
      Used in one-to-one relationships
      Prevents duplicates
